File: The SAA Pilots Association is fighting against the appointment of Zukisa Ramasia as interim CEO. JOHANNESBURG - The SAA Pilots Association is threatening to embark on a strike. Members are fighting against the appointment of Zukisa Ramasia as interim CEO. The association argues that Ramasia doesn't have the appropriate experience and acumen to successfully run the airline. READ: Unions threaten SAA shutdown It also wants underperforming management to be ousted to ensure the airline's recovery. The pilots are scheduled to meet with the board this week.